how much net profit

00:00:38.250 --> 00:00:39.770
she will make in a month.

00:00:39.770 --> 00:00:41.311
And that's what
we're thinking about.

00:00:41.311 --> 00:00:43.660
How many computers,
the minimum number she

00:00:43.660 --> 00:00:45.570
needs to sell in order
to make a net profit?

00:00:45.570 --> 00:00:48.770
So I'll write her
profit is going

00:00:48.770 --> 00:00:52.830
to be how much money she brings
in from selling the computers.

00:00:52.830 --> 00:00:56.370
And she makes $27 on
every computer she sells.

00:00:56.370 --> 00:01:00.870
So her profit is going to be
$27 times the number of computer

00:01:00.870 --> 00:01:01.410
she sells.

00:01:01.410 --> 00:01:05.550
She gets $27 per computer
times the number she sells.

00:01:05.550 --> 00:01:07.310
But we're not done yet.

00:01:07.310 --> 00:01:12.250
She still has expenses
